725989f-a.title: Queens: 172nd Street - Jamaica Avenue
725989f-a.text:
172nd Street, adjoining the S.E. corner of Jamaica Avenue, showing an old frame house. The house was owned by J. B. Way in 1891. The penants are flying from the 104th Field Artillery
Armory.
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS  March 25, 1932
